generalfeedback.text:
In one step eliminations (E2) at 6-membered saturated rings (chair conformation), the leaving group and the abstracted proton must be in a 1,2-diaxial arrangement. 

A: In trans-decalins, the chairs of the 6-membered rings can not invert, there is only one conformer. In this conformer, there is only one proton in 1,2-diaxial arrangement to the TsO- leaving group.
